in hepatocytes, as genes in the Gadd45 family are known to interact with cyclins, cyclin-dependent kinase inhibitors and p53 to alter progression through the cell cycle (Liebermann and Hoffman, 2008). Other CAR-mediated changes in gene expression such as those related to metabolism enzymes (e.g. CYP2B isoforms) lead to associative events in the liver such as increased CYP2B activity and/or protein, hepatocellular hypertrophy and increase liver weight.", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 14:49:01 +0000 2026"}